<section class="gc-glossary">
  <header class="gc-glossary__hero">
    <h1>Golden Collections Glossary of Temple & Classical Dance Jewellery</h1>
    <p>
      <strong>Golden Collections</strong> presents a curated glossary of
      <em>temple jewellery</em>, <em>Bharatanatyam &amp; Kuchipudi dance ornaments</em>, and
      <em>deity alankaram accessories</em>. Founded in 1961 by Shri Ashok Tunk and now led by
      his son <strong>Anil Tunk</strong> in Hyderabad, our family has been closely associated
      with dancers, gurus, and temples for over six decades. Use this guide to understand the
      heritage behind the most important jewellery terms.
    </p>
  </header>

  <nav class="gc-glossary__nav">
    <p><strong>Jump to section:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#gc-core">Core Concepts</a></li>
      <li><a href="#gc-head">Head Ornaments</a></li>
